
 Project Objectives

 Primary Objective

Build an end-to-end Retail Data Warehouse using SQL Server that integrates data from multiple business sources into a centralized analytical database, 
enabling interactive reporting and data-driven decision-making through Power BI.

 Technical Objectives

* Design a scalable Data Warehouse architecture using SQL Server.
* Build an ETL workflow to extract, transform, and load data from raw CSV files.
* Create staging tables to store and validate source data.
* Design a Star Schema with fact and dimension tables.
* Establish relationships using primary and foreign keys.
* Develop SQL views to simplify business reporting.
* Implement stored procedures for reusable data processing tasks.
* Optimize query performance using indexes and SQL best practices.

 Business Objectives

* Analyze sales performance across different years.
* Measure revenue, profit, and order trends.
* Identify top-performing products and categories.
* Evaluate customer purchasing behavior.
* Analyze regional sales performance.
* Monitor product returns and their impact on revenue.
* Provide executives with interactive dashboards for strategic decision-making.

 Reporting Objectives

The Power BI dashboards will provide insights into:

* Executive Sales Overview
* Customer Analytics
* Product Performance
* Regional Performance
* Return Analysis
* Year-over-Year Growth
* Monthly Sales Trends
* Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)

 Key Performance Indicators (KPIs)

The project will track the following KPIs:

* Total Sales
* Total Orders
* Total Customers
* Total Products Sold
* Total Returns
* Return Rate
* Average Order Value
* Sales Growth (%)
* Year-over-Year Growth
* Monthly Revenue
* Profit Margin
* Customer Retention Indicators

